reviews.text: First timer. Ordered the Cajun Chicken Filet. The fries were great- I love seasoned fries. They taste unique so it’s not a copy cat if other stores. The biscuit on the sandwich is harder than I like, but the filet is a good size for the price. It’s seasoned well. I love how the sauce pack is as  big as your palm. Also, shoot out to Sherry(?), for making my first time visit a positive experience. Great consumer service!

This place is fantastic! The customer service here is amazing. The manager Christina goes above and beyond to ensure guest satisfaction and that’s truly what keeps me coming back. Always with a smile on her face. She deserves me taking this moment to recognize her. The chicken and biscuits also deserve a review. I absolutely love this place!

The food here is horrible and disgusting. I took a bite and threw my food away. I wasted $8. i had the Cajun chicken biscuit. The chicken was fried hard and burnt. The biscuit was flat like a pancake. The dirty rice was like eating a spoonful of grease. The sweet tea was like the tea bag was never changed. I had to detox after a bite of everything. Never again and won't be returning.

Do not waste your time coming here. All of the employees were eating the food behind the counter, and had the nerve to serve cold food to the customers. How does that happen? This location has no reason to exist. If I could give this location no stars I would.

The employees here aren't very bright. I ordered a three-piece wing combo, a chicken sandwich, a large fry, and two sweet potato pies through DoorDash. The not so bright person who packed my order forgot the pies, large fries, and the biscuit that comes with my meal.

FOUND A GRAY HAIR IN THE FOOD!  I ordered a whole chicken yesterday. It didn’t taste very good and was dry.  So, not to waste it, I put gloves on and pulled the chicken added Mayo and as I was eating the chicken salad found this gray hair in my mouth 😖🤮. It’s gray and looks a bit curly.  I’m VERY irritated by this and will be sharing with the food department. DO BETTER!

Great chicken at a great price.  The green and red sauces are amazing.   Parking in the rear.  The food look tasty but I ate it all before I realized I wanted to leave a review.  If you are nearby - grab lunch here!

The food was delicious!  We bought the family special. It comes with two whole roaster chickens (they cut for you), five large sides, and a 2 liter beverage.  It fed our family and we had leftover chicken.  I am visiting from the West Coast. This will  definitely be a place I will visit everytime I come to the East Coast.

Local favorite for the longest. I can’t believe I haven’t reviewed this place.
Pro tip: add the chicken hot sauce to the rice. Yummy 😋

Food Order: Grilled Chicken tacos, steak tacos and fish tacos

Tacos were not good. I prefer a corn tortilla or at least homemade. The meat on all three were dry. It tasted like a soft taco from Taco Bell. I would not recommend getting the tacos.
Service was fast and cashier was friendly.

This has been my popeyes for a while. I made it there in time to not sit in that parking lot of a line that's always there. Thought I had scored. My order was simple. One meal deal from the app and a sweet tea. When I tell you this tea tasted like mop water. When I asked if I was mistakenly given unsweetened I just got a blank stare 😳  so I pulled off 🙄 but there's also that pothole past the podium that's gonna cost us all an  alignment and new tires. Chicken tenders were good. French fries were fried hard like the biscuits. Inedible waste of money for most of it.

I ordered a 2 piece with two sides using the app while in store so I asked the heavy set woman light skin somewhat about my order she got irritated and said she need a 4 digit code. I couldn't find it so I asked the manger lady with the dreads about it she said "what's the name I told her and she said it's right here baby" now she was very polite and humble thank you. But my thing is this the heavy set manage, if you don't like your job quit smh

The food was cold and old. The only thing by hat was fresh and hot were the biscuits. The staff was on their phones while helping the customers. Poor poor customer service. I’ll never go back there again. I’ll drive across town before I eat at my own local Popeyes.

This location no matter what time you go is the worst. Jesus himself couldn't save this location. Havent been here in months. I came in tonight (my dumb decision) and as per usual I got  ignored by almost everyone, im getting looked at but no one addressed me until a few minutes of me standing at the counter, and the lady in the gray hoodie clearly didn't want to be there. When you come to this location, It's guaranteed no less than 20 minutes for your food bc there is zero sense of urgency. Then after you've waited and got your food, don't you ask for anything else or they'll have an attitude like they've been waiting🤣. It's always at most 2 people at a time that actually have great customer service they aren't all horrible. But I say throw the whole store away

Why do it take so long. Got in line @450pm, got food at 520pm. I called, lady didnt even say I'm the manager, just how can I help you. I said do I need to come in is everything ok. She said something happened with a customer earlier and that the line is moving. Where the line moving to cause I'm still in it. As she was hanging up I heard her say what u expected it's a drive thru. I'm like my point in case is why does it take 30 mins to get a sandwich. You could have came out and told the customers that. You could gave a free frie or biscuit with people order (something), but u didnt. Ppl siting in line at the drive thru 30 plus mins. NO PROFESSIONALISM. NO COURTESY.

The BEST Rotisserie Chicken you’ll Ever have!! It’s always Hot and Fresh! Make sure you ask for EXTRA mild and hot sauce!( It sucks that they charge for more sauce but it’s so good you have too) Always a 10/10!
Decent food but the service and wait time are insane. They always have a huge staff but slow with the orders and the boys working the front don’t bother to inform you of the wait time.

This one is the best one in the area! The seasoning is definitely different than the other locations. I will still go to Temple Hills & Fort Washington but the Hill Crest one is my favorite. We get the fajitas with chicken, steak and shrimp and it’s delicious. This one also gives 3 tortillas where Temple Hills only gives 2. So you’ll need extras either way because the platters are huge. Hands down best fajitas in the area. Better than going to Uncle Julio’s Restaurant. It’s not cheap though.
Great place for takeout and usually enough for two meals!

my coworker ordered from silvestre chicken .
The food looked so good . when i got off work . I went to place to orders for dinner . The food is really good .

I wanted to be fair about my comments, as I do not share bogus or unauthentic reviews. Today, I purchased an entree and a salad (w/protein) while at my hair salon. Thinking that the meal would have been fresh and of quality, I opted to purchase the fried whiting dinner with macaroni and cheese, and cabbage.

We also purchased the blackened chicken salad. So, the salad had less than 4oz of chicken on it with a container full of lettuce. I did not realize this until after the gentlemen had left the salon or I would’ve sent it back with them. The fried whiting was soft with no crunch, not crispy at all (soggy) and the sides had not flavor.

After spending $40, we didn’t eat any of the food beyond the initial tasting and ended up purchasing dinner from another establishment. To the team who sells food outside of the actual restaurant, please be mindful of the quality of food you’re soliciting. If it’s not up to your standard meals, DO NOT SELL IT just to take back a profit. You lose repeat business that way and I would’ve definitely visited the restaurant, if the food was quality and appetizing.

Highly disappointed.

I've always enjoyed the food here, but as of late, there have been some issues.  I have been calling for brussel sprouts for atleast 2 weeks (No lie)  and they have been out of them.  What truly bothers me is I know this same lady that keeps answering the phone can see it's the same person calling asking the same question. She never offers anything else, not when they are coming in, or a side suggestion.  Just says "No" when asked.  It's as if they are no longer proud of what they are producing.  I'm not sure if they changed management or if they are losing focus but I hope they get it back soon.  I'm giving 3 stars because the food is still good, however; the customer service is trash.  To the owner: I offer customer services classes and would be happy to give your cashiers some tips and tricks to help. Empathy goes a long way and because I feel like I'm bothering you guys when I call, I don't want to call again.  Come on Food for Life!  Don't do us like that.

We had been longtime customers. Unfortunately, today's meals were sadly disappointing. I understand the rise in food costs have to be passed on to the consumer. But this is no excuse for lowering the quality of the food.

First off, please inform customers your brussel sprouts include cheese. I am allergic to milk, unable to have cheese, and this was the first huge issue. Secondly, my blackened salmon smelled bad. I thought to myself, dont eat that. But, I took a few bites anyway...bad idea. My stomach is regretting it completely. Lastly, the warm demeanor we use to receive when we came in was definitely absent. I felt like I was visiting just another carryout. Deeply disappointed and sad that I had to write this review. Please regain your commitment to quality. Your longtime customers miss you!!!

I spent $19.00 for lunch this is the worst food I ever tasted. I wouldn't feed this food to my dog. The greens were Horrible!!! the salmon look like it can from the dollar store and the mac & cheese is watery. On top of that I called to the store to inform them of the situation hoping that the they would at least  apologize for wasting my time and money. The young lady response was we don't do refunds. Wow I will never order from them again!!!!!

I used to love Food for Life more than 5 years ago. It was very clean, the staff was very nice and seemed to represented the natural food theme of the carry out in a positive way. The food was always good. I was there almost every week. Then suddenly, over time, the front staff changed to some uncaring, unpleasant, unprofessional, hostile acting workers. The cook staff seemed to change too. I noticed some things going on in back that made me question the food service preparation process. The quality of the food also began to decline. The places overall physical appearance start to decline. I really wish the current owner would bring this carry out back up to the high quality venue that was first started years ago.

Ribs were lightly seasoned, tender.8/10
I order mumbo sauce instead of barbecue. Don’t do that .2/10 and last but not least the greens we’re  nicely cooked with no seasoning. I will order the ribs again!

My friend kept saying he wanted ribs and chicken so we googled “food near me” while we were on a quick trip in MD. Let me tell you this pace did not disappoint!! The chicken was tender and juicy and the ribs were seasoned to perfection. Definitely going on my revisit list next time I’m out that way!!
Rib tips lunch special... great lunch deal always great customer service ...
Ribs and smoked wings combo was bomb. I choose Ribs and things over Johnny Boys. The seafood salad is not great but definitely better then Johnny boys

The food is bad, really bad. Everything I
ordered: barbecue chicken wings was hard, mac and cheese was very dry, baked beans (from a can) extremely Horrible I threw it away. I will Never Ever again waste my money on this business. I wish I could give it a 0. The best part of my meal was the drink.

This is my favorite shell there's always a lot of pumps available I don't really interact with the staff because I have the fuel rewards app it allows me to pump my gas and pay from my phone The only other time I go Inside is when I want to buy Snacks for bonus points in the app When I didn't go in there the staff did not give me a problem

The staff member named Buddy work the 11-4 shift is rude had my son 16 ( had him cornered out of view of camera)as I waited for him in my car lift his shirt told him to pull is pants down because he is stealing my daughter went in to see what was taking so long she walked in on this as she approached asked what he was doing he got in her face. I went in was told he was,pressing charges on me because I asked for his mangers name or owner. I'm currently filing charges against him for sexual harassment against a minor and harassment currently looking for the owner this is not acceptable not all black teenagers steal.

Always bunch of dirty teens standing around the front asking for money . The mini store they have is so cramp easy for someone to pick pocket you pumps never have paper for your receipt the service is so so . and they never change the water for cleaning your window I had slime all over my windows had to end up going straight to a car wash after getting gas this place sucks big time.

I have been observing this Shell financial business with the community it's serving for years. Everything in the store is cheap when using a credit card. Everything in the store is expensive when using cash. Tobacco products are very high with cash, cheap when payment is used with credit. Something to analyze.

The New guy that works midshift..young thin guy...I'll be getting his name soon...is rude and Discriminatory..And You all will be hearing more about him.THEY may not know about the Bp kettering situation but there day is coming...Soon!!!!They are located in a primarily Black neighborhood ,and thrive on Our money(not mines anymore) @ treat US like trash...PLEASE STOP FRANCHISING THIS BUSINESS!!!!!
Ordered fish sandwiche,, tarter sauce had weird texture... I got sick 🤮 almost died. Mexican women had ridiculous smile on face when she handed me my food like she knew she hitted me with the hawk

On 12/4/22, I went here at around 11:45pm. While at drive thru, I attempted to place my order but the female Spanish lady was the most unprofessional, disrespectful employee I’ve met while at McDonald’s.

I gave her my code for $1 large french fry and had to say it twice as she was busy talking to someone in the  background and totally ignoring me. So, when I said hello loudly she said, “ Go ahead with your order. I gave her the code again and she said come to the window. As I tried to tell her I want to order something else as well she totally ignored me and eventually responded and said come to the window. I, didn’t understand why I needed to come to the window and have my order taken as others where placing their orders. Not to mention, there were several cars in front of me at this point so I left.

As I decided to leave and go to another McDonald’s, I tried taking a photo of the rude female employee. When she saw me she laughed and walked away from the window and had a male employee assist the customers and never came back. She is definitely a poor representative of McDonald’s and such behavior shouldn’t be allowed or tolerated. She need to be removed from the drive thru and not allowed to interact with customers.

I, decided to go another McDonald’s on Chavez Lane and  the experience was totally different. The staff from placing my order to receiving my order were professional and friendly.

Worst big mac ever!!!! McDonald's should be ashamed, if the meat gets any thinner it would be nonexistant and the patty isn't even big enough around to even cover the bun guess they need to decrease the bun size so people won't notice it as much. Just sad used to be an awesome sandwich. The staff at this store are the best!!! Always friendly and smiling and great at what they do. You should give them a raise with the money you are saving on the meat!
Not big on McDonald's like I was as a kid but my grandson loves Happy Meals with extra fries 😋

Food was correct but cold. There was no greeting. They just handed me my food. I did a mobile order to speed up the process and when I came to the window, they informed me the machine was down. They couldn't give me a refund and I didn't see where to get a refund from the app. Very disappointing 😞

Went through the drive thru at 8:45pm  after the man took my order all I can heat him say was "man I am about to leave I am not doing this s*** anymore". Then he still doesn't turn off his headset and all I heard was the workers in the background chatting it up while I still wait to be told my total and to pull up. I pulled after waiting 5 minutes off because I don't need to give my money to an establishment that's rude and ghetto and clearly no customer service. Not to mention when I do come here the drive thru is extremely slow. Never again.

It took forever to get app to work. Asked a manager to help and was denied.
On top of all that, after finally getting the app to work I ordered 2 sandwich only. They forgot to put a whole sandwich in my bag. Had to go back and wait in long drive thru line again because lobby is closed at 11am.

Service was awful.

The staff weren't wearing masks. I asked fir a manager an some young dirty looking male appeared saying he was yhe.manager. I asked where the older gentleman was that used to manage that store and was informed he no longer worked there. I asked the young manager why he didn't have his "very long" UNKEPT DREADLOCKS pulled back in a rubber band or in a hairnet,  he said it wasn't required. The service was beyond SLOW.  I will never go back there.

This restaurant seems to always be slow and low staffed. The staff isn’t rude but they are nonchalant. They could be more attentive to costumers, especially delivery drivers.

My review isn’t based on just one experience, I’ve come here multiple times to place orders and to pick up orders. Each time they’re slow. The wait time is at least 15-20 minutes each visit, so get comfy.

They have no strategy for orders placed thru delivery apps expect to wait in line, which takes up a delivery drivers time to get to another order.

The actual store isn’t open so it’s just drive thru, hence the long wait.

Plus, They’re always out of specific items. And  there’s is always some homeless people standing nearby asking for money.
This Wendy's has redone its whole staff, the new staff is very quick and friendly. I would definitely go back to them now. Thanks

I am DONE with this place. If they're not forgetting something from my order stuff is undercooked, the dumplings are hit or miss. The dumplings were so good in my first few orders, but in the last few months they fell off. Recently  the dumpling filling tasted NOTHING like pork, idk wth it was. This time the dumpling filling is RAW on the inside and the dough is undercooked. They beef and broccoli sauce is the same as their mumbo sauce, can't even make a brown gravy.
Idk wth they're doing over there but the quality and standard of the food is horrible now, they won't be getting no more of my coins.

Not going to lie..I was going to sit on this review..but I hate gatekeepers..so let’s get into it!

I’m not sure why this place is rated so low…because I have received nothing but delicious eats from here! I heard about this carry out from a friend. It says a lot because WE DO NOT EAT DIRTY, GREASY CARRY-OUT. I understand carry out is not a culinary phenomenon..but WE AT LEAST try to eat at good hood ones. This is one! The steak and cheese are so bomb! Meat is always falling out just bc there is so much! The shaved steak isn’t super fatty like other places are. The Chinese food..delicious! The shrimp in the shrimp and broccoli is clean! Shrimp basket shrimp..clean! (No poop veins). Steak and Cheese egg roll…NOT GREASY! I haven’t had the wings yet..but judging by their Mumbo sauce..I know it’ll hit. Don’t be fooled on the outside..the steps are a little wonky..but it’s all good.If you must order carry out ..order Good East.

*the owner usually has her kids (older boy and young girl) behind the counter..be kind and gentle with them. ☺️

Will upload pictures next time..I ALWAYS dog the food before I can grab the camera.

I don't come for the service or atmosphere, i come for the food, and it's excellent. Been coming here a long time, and it's my kind of Chinese food. Surprisingly, the pizza is awesome too. The Good East Meat Combo Pizza isn't on the menu, but it's amazing.
Chicken was a little salty. Jumbo sweet. Not the bbq kind. Overall good 5 wings with fries was around $11.50.
Good food, childhood restaurant gone bad though, last order they don't even pay me my $20 back, they had just drove off. Not cool 😠

Ordered the crab cake sandwich and cream of crab soup - probably the worst seafood items I've tasted. The crab cake was soft and mushy, the coleslaw was warm and bland with too much mayo, the soup tasted and looked similar to Campbell's condensed. Paid almost $50 for food to throw in the trash.

Here to pickup a grub hub order. They state they close at 8:00, however they closed thier doors at 7:30. I have gathered they stop taking orders at 7:00 and 8:00 is what time the employees leave after cleaning up. This is the second time this has happened. It would be ok if they would communicate this better and I didn’t have to drive 35 minutes to get here

Thursday, January 5th, I stopped at Cameron's in Marlow Heights Maryland. I purchased 1 lb. of steamed shrimp and a whiting fillet sandwich. The shrimp were DRY! Absolutely no juice! In the display case there were king crab legs. Where there should have been white moist meat showing in the body, there was the color gray and a dried look! In other pieces the color was a dried brown!! I had to throw away my shrimp. Will NEVER give them my $$ again!!!

I thought I ordered the Ultimate Seafood Platter with croaker bone fish. I'm not sure what I got for $23.99. You judge for yourself. However,  I did get a king crab leg for $54. It was a pretty good size too. I will probably be going back for the king crab but I will pass on the dinners.
I bought my food here and I did not let them prepare it I fried it myself but it was absolutely delicious.,..

Was in the area and craving Chinese food on the late night. Glad I stopped here. I ordered a teriyaki chicken appetizer and two shrimp egg rolls. I was not a fan of the sauce they put on the teriyaki chicken, but the chicken itself was crispy and delicious. I just wiped the sauce off with a napkin. I also would not have considered it a teriyaki sauce, it was more of a barbecue sauce. Shrimp egg rolls were good, although I would have liked them to have been a bit more crispy. Only like two little shrimps in them also. And the iced tea and lemonade mix was delicious. But the ice smelled a little funky at the end of the cup. Overall would recommend and would return

The food was mediocre at best. Service was extremely slow I waited about 25 minutes for dumplings, chicken wings, and fried rice. Overall this was a less then desirable experience I will probably never return. Also after making me wait almost a half hour for a simple order they wanted to charge me extra for more sauce which was the icing on the never return again cake. There are enough Chinese places nearby with better food and better service that you should try instead of this one
I was gonna leave a bad review . . . Look at the pics . . . Eat at your own risk
WHEN EVERY OTHER FOOD PLACE IS CLOSED THEY ARE OPEN TILL LATE NIGHTS. THATS RESPECT AND THE FOOD BE GOOD TOO

Food was ok , my aunt seemed to love the fried crab cakes, my fav was the 6 chicken wings with general tso’s sauce on the side it’s extra but worth it. Also love the mozzarella sticks fresh breaded n cheesy. Shrimp lomein imma rate 31/2 out 5 only because it could have had a little more veggies. They stay open late so it’s a great choice . Cheesecake 4/5 . Good fast service and the also have chopsticks . Will definitely go back and try more menu items I wasn’t disappointed in taste or quantity 5/5.

Working over at NOAA isn't bad, but their cafe is just flat out bad. I walk over here and it's like the gates of heaven have opened up (in comparison). Food selection is great, quality is good, prices are average. I just wish NSOF had at least some fresh food.

Way too expensive for what you get.  Often times the food isn’t ideally cooked.  Don’t bother going on a Friday.  If you’re reading this, odds are you don’t have many alternatives due to the fact that Eurest has an effective monopoly.

Staff is generally nice though
A clean cafeteria with average, if a bit expensive, food. Self service buffet is hit or miss with all meat picked from the main entree if you arrive late.
Institution food at it finest! $8 per ounce salad bar is all encompassing and wilted. Not much to enjoy on a daily basis.
Decent cafeteria experience, some specials offered during the week. Really, the best you could ask for from a cafeteria.

My teammate and I just finished a 5k and wanted to refuel with healthy options. Recently read an article saying it's Maryland Vegan Restaurant month and this place was listed close to where we finished our workout.
We arrived 10 minutes after opening and there were others who already placed their order. Chef Chris greeted us warmly at the counter to take our order. After viewing the menu on the TV my teammate decided on the fried oyster mushrooms with roasted root vegetables and sweet potato tots. I ordered the soul daddy burger, old bay fries, and mac & cheese. We shared the smoked sweet chili chicken wings and ordered a steak & cheese to go. The total was $70.
Didn't take note of the wait time but was satisfied when I got my food. Chef Chris caught me doing my food dance. I really enjoyed the soul daddy & fries. My teammate said the fried oyster mushrooms were delicious and even recommended it to another customer who walked in. The steak and cheese was delivered to a relative who said it was good and it wasn't mentioned to be a vegan steak and cheese. The mac & cheese was my least favorite possibly because uses carrots and I enjoy cashew mac.
I would go back to try the yard bird, jerk chicken wrap, and the smoked ribs. I'd be excited to try a milkshake also.

Where do I begin. The establishment is clean and the customer service was great! Now for the food it was AWESOME! A family of five we spent $111.30 and it was worth every penny. The ribs, fried chicken, Brussel sprouts, braised kale, jerk chicken wrap, steak and cheese all delicious. The ribs were so good, we order some to go. This was our first time but won't be our last.  We will definitely make the trip from Fort Washington to dine.

A great vegan restaurant to have in the community!

#blackowned
Some the of best vegan food I ever ate. The owner Chris is a sweetheart ! A must go to vegan spot. You can tell that everything was cooked with love.🥰😍

Love it here! Their brick and mortar location recently opened, perfect for takeout or dine in! Menu highlights include drummies, jerk chick’n wrap, oyster mushroom fried chick’n, and basically everything else!
By far some of the best vegan food I have ever taste! I will be back.

They cannot provide a sandwich that looks like their photos. They use chicken tenders instead of full chicken pieces for their sandwiches.

When I called about my order they essentially told me I ordered the wrong thing but I didn’t. I don’t think I’ll be trying them again. Because if the tenders where good i would have been fine but they weren’t.

Total rip off. Pictures on Uber Eats were a complete lie and misleading. $14 for a chicken sandwich, and chicken was smaller than my palm. Fries were like a stale version of McDonald's. Bun was large, and sauce was good (although it was supposed to be pimento cheese). Wife's sandwich had small square of charred bacon. Everything was falsely advertised.

What the what?! False advertising! They are frozen patties that you could buy in the freezer section of a grocery store! The Uber pics are not even close! Think high school cafeteria chicken sandwich - then think worse! I couldn’t believe what I received! 1 star is generous!
Ordered 2 different sandwiches, got 2 of the same sandwich. Somehow both were wrong.
I ordered from this place on UberEats and literally thought I was being pranked. My entire order was wrong and the food is a joke. Better to spend your money at ChicfilA or Popeyes.

name: Southern Peach Bbq
vicinity: 3609 Saint Barnabas Road Suite B, Suitland-Silver Hill

reviews.text:
For my 31st birthday, part of what I did to enjoy myself was order out via GrubHub. I searched and loved the food of Southern Peach 🍑 BBQ and it is a Black-owned business so I had to support it! For February, Black History Month I'm supporting all types of Black-owned businesses (especially restaurants.)

Of course, they didn't disappoint. After 3 days it lasted, all the food. I bought $70 dollars worth including a tip. The cheesesteak, peach lemonade, 2 wraps (General Tso and Chipotle), three sides of fries (each main came with a choice of side), and 🍤 fried shrimp I'd say it was a good buy.

Thank you for the flavor, longevity, and making my birthday one to remember 💛🌟🙌🏾.

This place should simply close its doors for good. I ordered via Uber eats. I never got the side of corn, which was my main side. The hush puppies are completely burnt. And I didn’t get my drink. I ordered the rice bowl. This dished, consisted of chicken, rice, and broccoli. Not only did it look sloppy . It tasted horrible. I don’t know who they have in there cooking, but I’m from down south. We would laugh you out of town, if you tried to sell this garbage there. No wonder your prices are so high. You all can’t make any money. Do yourself a favor, stop selling food. It’s not what you’re good at.

Shout out to Southern Peach for serving at the Blerdcon event this weekend. They were my life saver when one of the other trucks were taking too long to serve. The staff are so friendly, and they keep the line moving and keep the food coming. I tried their smoked wings and strawberry lemonade today, the smoked wings were burning hot when brought out, and full of flavor, I had no idea they were served with sauce, but whatever that sauce is was delicious. The strawberry lemonade was a nice size portion, and wasn't overly sweet. I'm glad they are near my house because I'll be going back.

This is just horrible how do you charge someone all that money for this not only do it not look appealing it don’t taste good neither. Also look at the amount of food smh I don’t know how they up and running. Complete Trash

reviews.author_name: Keemah's World Yall just livin in it
reviews.text: I’m not trying to be too picky but naahh I’ll pass. So I order the fried shrimp. When I go to soul food places I expect to get fried shrimp not shrimp you would get from captain D’s or long John silver. The food was bland this didn’t taste like soul food cause I didn’t actually get anything that they could put their soul into. The lemonade was nasty. Wasn’t sweet just tasted like sour water. Unfortunately I would never try this place again.

Capitol Hill was my junior teens are coming up around the DMV always wondering or dreaming about a career that I can help my city now on that I have been in all girls and sections of the city it's a struggle for everyone DC is a real busy City during the daytime so someone have to step up so what I did I stepped my game up with roadside lines 24 hour fleet division in the DMV to help people out with roadside and tires so anyone you lock out jumps down battery change brakes and rotors you have someone that really will help you system issues remember boots on the ground we are steppers and working all kinds of weather we get down with the good down go to our website's Grand Auto rescue

For a very long time this restaurant has had a problem in keeping its food hot.  However, to my surprise today the food was hot, but for some reason, the serving plates were cold.  So, by the time you place your food on a cold plate, the hot food is no longer hot...maybe warm at best.  This  cold food scenario has kept me away from this restaurant.  I just decided to give it another chance this evening.

The next problem is with the wait staff.  The restaurant appears to have only two people, regardless of the number of people that are being served.   The stress of this problem shows clearly with the male waiter, who always gives off a negative and unpleasant vibe.

The restroom area has a atrocious odor coming from it.  It smells like something terrible is breeding in that area.  The smell is bad enough to make you give back your meal.  The restroom needs to be professionally sanitized.  I wish I could have given a more pleasant review, but management needs to make these issues a priority.
